news.title: Bajaj Finance exploring options to list its housing finance arm
news.para: The company’s consolidated net profit rose by 21% to Rs. 3,825 crore, supported by a 28% increase in net interest income in the fourth quarter. Net interest income jumped to Rs. 8,013 crore from Rs. 6,254 crore a year ago.

news.title: DTCP razes eight illegal buildings in joint operation in Gurugram
news.para: Yadav said eight under-construction houses were razed, of which three were demolished up to the ground level, along with 250 jhuggis, with the help of 50 labourers and earthmovers.

news.title: London's Canary Wharf sees $1.5 billion slashed from property values
news.para: Canary Wharf Group - which is joint owned by investors Brookfield and the Qatar Investment Authority - said in its 2023 earnings that its overall property portfolio declined in value to 6.8 billion pounds from 8 billion.

news.title: Holcim posts 7.8% rise in operating profit in Q1 2024
news.para: The Swiss company is planning to separate and spin off its North America business next year. In the first quarter to end-March the region saw a 0.3% dip in local currency sales.

news.title: Real estate deals worth $5.4 million terminated in Europe in Q1 2024: MSCI
news.para: Europe's commercial property sector has been hammered in recent years by a punishing rise in debt costs and tumbling prices, exacerbated by some offices and high streets emptying after the pandemic.

news.title: KKR to buy $1.64 billion student housing portfolio from Blackstone's REIT
news.para: "This transaction is an excellent outcome for BREIT's investors and demonstrates the strong demand for the high-quality assets," Jacob Werner, co-head of Americas acquisitions for Blackstone Real Estate, said in a statement.

news.title: DMCI Holdings to buy Cemex Holdings Philippines for $305.6 million
news.para: Cement manufacturing will be a good, strategic addition to our business portfolio," DMCI Chairman Isidro Consunji said in a statement.

news.title: Germany's Adler Group renegotiates debt as real estate deals slow
news.para: Adler, one of Germany's biggest landlords, is fighting a liquidity crisis triggered by a downturn in the domestic property market, rising energy and building prices caused by Russia's invasion of Ukraine and the fallout from the COVID-19 pandemic.

news.title: Kone's operating profit up 10.1% to $280 million in Q1 2024
news.para: China accounts for about 25% of Kone's business, but the company's new equipment division has been struggling to contend with protracted property sector woes in the country since 2021.

news.title: Provident Housing secures Rs 1,150 crore investment from HDFC Capital
news.para: Provident Housing and HDFC Capital collaboration will add an additional 6.2 million sq ft of new residential projects with a combined gross development value (GDV) of Rs 17,100 crore.

news.title: ACC posts net profit of Rs 944.84 crore in Q4 FY24
news.para: ACC's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 5,528.45 crore, a growth of 12.59 per cent from Rs 4,910.06 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Three people booked for duping developer over sale of land in Thane
news.para: The builder alleged that he and his family paid Rs 42 lakh to the accused in connection with the deal but the accused neither got the land transferred nor refunded the money.

news.title: Anant Raj's net profit up 73.43% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Anant Raj's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 453.12 crore, a growth of 56.31 per cent from Rs 289.89 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Edelweiss Alternatives' RYP Fund completes acquisition of MMTP Projects for over Rs 1,500 crore
news.para: RYP fund's portfolio has scaled up to 1.8 million sq ft gross leasable area (GLA) in Bengaluru and Gurugram. With this acquisition, RYP currently holds assets valued over Rs 2,500 crore.

news.title: Sumadhura Group acquires 40 acres land for about Rs 800 crore in Bengaluru
news.para: Sumadhura Group plans to develop four residential projects on these sites - three in the east and one in south west Bengaluru over the next five years with an estimated potential of six million sq ft of saleable area.

news.title: Buyer sentiment strong in housing segment, says Magicbricks survey
news.para: The real estate platform unveiled its flagship Housing Sentiment Index (HSI) report, reflecting a positive outlook for the residential real estate market, with an overall HSI of 149.

news.title: ED raids Tulsiani Group as part of money laundering investigation
news.para: An office premise in the Gomti Nagar area of Lucknow, linked to a family member of BJP MLA from Harraiya (Basti) Ajay Singh, was also covered by the agency as part of the probe against the Tulsiani Group.
